==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inscient
<hw>In"scient</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n"sh⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insciens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, ignorant. See <er>In-</er> not,
and <er>Scient</er>, <er>Science</er>.]</ety> <def>Having little or no
knowledge; ignorant; stupid; silly.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>N.
Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inscient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inscient
<hw>In"scient</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + L.
<ets>sciens</ets> knowing.]</ety> <def>Having knowledge or insight;
intelligent.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gaze on, with <qex>inscient</qex> vision, toward the sun.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insconce</ent>⟦br⟧
